1-120.Certified public accountant; reexamination fee.

The board shall charge fees as established by the board for reexaminations under the Public Accountancy Act. Such fees shall not exceed fifty dollars for each subject in which a person is reexamined. An applicant for the reexamination may be required to pay additional fees as charged by and remitted or paid to a third party for administering the reexamination, if required by the board.

SourceLaws 1957, c. 1, § 15, p. 60;Laws 1976, LB 619, § 6;Laws 1979, LB 278, § 2;Laws 1984, LB 473, § 10;Laws 1991, LB 75, § 9;Laws 1997, LB 114, § 17;Laws 2003, LB 214, § 4;Laws 2009, LB31, § 10.
